file=Brand Studio/weave/logical/book-requirements.md · h=name: weave-logical-book-requirements\ntype: logical\nstatus: built — inherits from Shared OS (2026-07-15)\nassigned_agent: weave (Brand Studio / Storytelling)\ndate_added: 2026-07-07\ndate_filled: 2026-07-15\n · p:=Logical artifacts are Python scripts in `Shared OS/logical/` (playbook §13.5). Weave inherits the department-shared `marketing_laws.py`. All dedicated scripts are paywall-blocked pending Route D .md files. This file is the only file in this folder.\n · tb=\| # \| Script \| Source Book 1 \| Book 1 URL \| Source Book 2 \| Book 2 URL \| Route \| · tb=\|---\|--------\|--------------\|------------\|---------------\|------------\|-------\| · tb=\| 1 \| `marketing_laws.py` \| Ries & Trout, *The 22 Immutable Laws of Marketing* (1993) \| [archive.org](https://archive.org/details/22immutablelawso00alri) — FREE \| Cialdini, *Pre-Suasion* (2016) \| [archive.org](https://archive.org/details/presuasionrevolu0000cial) — FREE \| B \| · s(o:Scripts (Shared OS/logical/)=Additional free sources: Pareto (1896), Marshall (1890), Bernays (1928), Campbell (1949), Zipf (1949), Lasswell (1948), Hick (1952), Zajonc (1968), Von Restorff (1933). 10 free books/papers total.\n · tb=\| Script \| Source Book \| Book URL \| Why Weave Needs It \| · tb=\|--------\|------------\|----------\|---------------------\| · tb=\| `marketing_laws.py` \| Ries & Trout + Cialdini + 8 free sources \| See above \| Grounds narrative structure judgments with Campbell's monomyth, Lasswell's communication model, and Cialdini's persuasion sequencing \| · tb=\| Previously Flagged (0.6) \| Status \| Script \| · tb=\|--------------------------\|--------\|--------\| · tb=\| structural judgments — "chapter out of sequence," "act should end" — flagged craft-based \| ✅ Cleared \| `marketing_laws.py` — Campbell monomyth reference (hero's journey: departure-initiation-return maps to act structure), `lasswell_model` (narrative communication: who tells what story to whom) \| · tb=\| arc template sections — practitioner-distilled, not theory-verified \| ✅ Cleared \| `marketing_laws.py` — `bernays_consent` (narrative persuasion ethics: every story arc has a consent dimension), `cialdini_commitment_consistency` (narrative escalation = commitment sequence) \| · tb=\| guide-vs-hero casting — craft rule without formal grounding \| ✅ Cleared \| `marketing_laws.py` — Campbell monomyth (the hero's guide archetype), `cialdini_authority` (the guide must have credible authority) \| · sts:Skills to Script Mapping=- **brand-storytelling** — imports `marketing_laws.py` (`lasswell_model` for story communication check, `bernays_consent` for narrative ethics)\n- **story-arcs** — imports `marketing_laws.py` (Campbell monomyth reference for act structure, `cialdini_commitment_consistency` for narrative escalation)\n · tb=\| Script \| Blocked By \| Source Needed \| · tb=\|--------\|-----------\|---------------\| · tb=\| Dedicated Miller StoryBrand extraction \| Paywalled book \| Miller, *Building a StoryBrand* (SB7 framework: character-problem-guide-plan-CTA-failure-success) \| · tb=\| Dedicated McKee extraction \| Paywalled book \| McKee, *Story* (story values, progressive complications, act design, the gap) \| · tb=\| Dedicated Campbell full extraction \| Paywalled book \| Campbell, *The Hero with a Thousand Faces* (full monomyth beyond the public-domain reference) \| · sp:Still Pending=These require Route D .md files from paywalled sources before extraction can proceed.\n